### PROPOSAL
## NOT A PULL REQUEST


I had a problem with creating custom serdes for my custom models. I realized that I make lots of boiler plate code, so I came up with `BaseSerde` class, so creating new custom serdes comes to:
```
public class CustomSerde extends BaseSerde<Custom> {
  
  private CustomSerde() {
    super(Custom.class);
  }
  
  public static Serde<Custom> serde() {
    return new CustomSerde();
  }

}
```
And then you can simply do: `CustomSerde.serde()`

What do you think of this approach? Or maybe there is some way simpler that I don't know about?
